/**
  Math for the indicator we are using to show if a thread is pinned as part of
  #exp-pinned-comments! This icon sits in the top-right corner of the cluster
  element and should shift as the radius expands with a scale transformation:

          , - ~ ~ ~ - ,
      , '               ' ,     ,
    ,                       ,     ,
    ,                         ,     ,
  ,                   r1      ,     ,
  ,             ------------- , --- ,
  ,             |             , |   ,
    ,            ------- r2 - , --  ,
    ,                       ,     ,
      ,                  , '
        ' - , _ _ _ ,  '

  r2 = 1.1 * r1 (or 1.2, in the case of .emphasized)
  d1 and d2 are equal to 2r1 and 2r2, respectively

  Since we're shifting the top-left coordinates of the pin indicator, we need
  to calculate the delta between the two radii, and derive the x/y from the
  hypotenuse of the triangle created

  ((scaleFactor * d1 - d1) / 2)^2 = delta^2
  delta = (scaleFactor * d1 - d1) / 2 / sqrt(2)
*/

                const filterValue = button.getAttribute('data-filter');

                portfolioCards.forEach(card =&gt; {
                    if (filterValue === 'all') {
                        card.style.display = 'block';
                        setTimeout(() =&gt; {
                            card.style.opacity = '1';

                                card.style.opacity = '1';

                            }, 10);

                            card.style.transform = 'scale(0.8)';
                            setTimeout(() =&gt; {
